Your first API token — 2 minutes to set up

recuerd0 works best when your AI tools can read from it. An API token makes that possible.

Three steps:

1. Go to Settings → Access Tokens
2. Click "New Token" — give it a name and choose a permission level
3. Copy the token and store it somewhere safe (you won't see it again)

That's it. Once you have a token, the CLI and any AI integration can authenticate with your account.

